rn]	G [Return]	[CTRL-C]	G 400	[CTRL-C](2) Load smpscl3.abs to address 6002000H.	l ;r:smpscl3.abs [return](3) Execute with G 6002000 [Return].[Functions Used]	SCL_Vdp2Init	SCL_SetFrameInterval	SCL_SetColRamMode	SCL_InitConfigTb	SCL_SetConfig	SCL_SetCycleTable	SCL_SetPriority	SCL_Open	SCL_Close	SCL_MoveTo	SCL_Move	SCL_Scale	SCL_DisplayFrame	SCL_InitLineParamTb	SCL_SetLineParam[Comments]The function SetVblank and variables PadData1 and PadData2 are contained in the directory V_BLANK as samples of setting interrupt processing routines.* smpsmp5.c[Title]Display 2 rotation scroll planes (RBG0, RBG1)[Description]Display 256 color bit-mapped characters on rotation scroll plane 0. Displays a 256 color image that includes the line color screen on rotation scroll plane 1 in cell format. Control pad 1 is used to move the image.[Instructions](1) Initialize the boot ROM with the following commands	RS [Return]	G [Return]	[CTRL-C]	G 400	[CTRL-C](2) Load smpscl5.abs to address 6002000H.	l ;r:smpscl2.abs [return](3) Execute with G 6002000 [Return].(4) Pad operation:[Control Pad 1]Use control pad 1 to manipulate scroll plane	START button: Initialize rotation angle and position	Up on D-pad: Move on Y axis	Down on D-pad: Move on Y axis	Left on D-pad: Move on X axis	Right on D-pad: Move on X axis	R button: Move on Z axis	L button: Move on Z axis	X button: Rotate on X axis	Y button: Rotate screen	Z button: Rotate on Z axis	A button: Select RGB0	B button: Select RGB1	C button: Change RGB1 priority (above or below RBG0)[Functions Used]	SCL_Vdp2Init	SCL_SetSpriteMode	SCL_SetColRamMode	SCL_SetBack	SCL_InitRotateTable	SCL_InitVramConfigTb	SCL_SetVramConfig	SCL_InitConfigTb	SCL_SetConfig	SCL_SetPriority	SCL_AllocColRam	SCL_SetColRam	SCL_SetShadowBit	SCL_SetLncl	SCL_EnableLineCol	SCL_SetColMixRate	SCL_SetFrameInterval	SCL_Open	SCL_Close	SCL_MoveTo	SCL_Move	SCL_RotateTo	SCL_Rotate	SCL_Scale	SCL_DisplayFrame[Comments]The function SetVblank and variables PadData1 and PadData2 are contained in the directory V_BLANK as samples of setting interrupt processing routines.[Cautions]None***************************end of file***************************